The paper deals with the problem of robots manipulating articulated objects in human environments, which is a core problem in robotics (cs.RO). The proposed method uses RGB-D images to capture object motion, which is a common technique in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also incorporates natural language descriptions to convey knowledge of manipulation models, which falls under natural language processing (cs.CL). The method uses a probabilistic language model, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and the paper also presents a multimodal learning framework, which is a common approach in artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
